                  "options": [
                    "<div>   <strong>0 — No Anxiety</strong><br>   <span>I feel relaxed and calm. There is nothing preoccupying my thoughts.</span> </div>",
                    "<div>   <strong>1 — Mild Anxiety</strong><br>   <span>I feel slight anxiety about one or two things; I can distract myself easily from these thoughts; I’m able to function normally at work or school, at home, in my hobbies, and in my social life despite these thoughts.</span> </div>",
                    "<div>   <strong>2 — Moderate Anxiety</strong><br>   <span>I am anxious around half of the time; I have difficulty getting thoughts causing me anxiety out of my head but I am still able to distract myself from my anxious thoughts at times; I am still able to function normally at work or school, at home, in my hobbies, and in my social life.</span> </div>",
                    "<div>   <strong>3 — Moderately Severe Anxiety</strong><br>   <span>     I am anxious most of the time; I find it difficult to distract myself from these thoughts;     this affects my concentration and focus and has started to impact my work or school, home life,     hobbies, and social life; I avoid some places or activities because of worry; I have headaches     and feel tired.   </span> </div>",
                    "<div>   <strong>4 — Severe Anxiety</strong><br>   <span>     I am anxious almost all the time; I cannot control my anxiety levels; I cannot function in two     or more areas (work/school, home, hobbies, socialising); I feel keyed up or on edge; I cannot     leave the house due to my anxiety; I am short of breath with chest tightness or pain, have     digestive issues, feel tired, and feel tense with muscle aches and pains.   </span> </div>",
                    "<div>   <strong>5 — Extreme Anxiety</strong><br>   <span>     I am anxious all the time; I am having a panic attack or feel like I will; I have intense physical     symptoms in my chest, digestive system, head, muscles, and joints causing significant distress; I feel paralysed; I feel something terrible is going to happen.   </span> </div>"
